{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef\/pushThreadDefault()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLib","externalID":"s:4GLib19MainContextProtocolPAAE17pushThreadDefaultyyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib14MainContextRefV","title":"pushThreadDefault()","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}]},"abstract":[{"text":"Acquires ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(such as most "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html"},{"text":"-based I\/O) which are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"started in this thread to run under "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"text":" and deliver their","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changes the context returned by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not the one returned by [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], so it does not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"affect the context used by functions like [func"},{"code":"GLib.idle_add","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef\/MainContextProtocol-Implementations"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextref\/pushthreaddefault()"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pushThreadDefault"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Normally you would call this function shortly after creating a new"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"thread, passing it a [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] which will be run by a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] in that thread, to set a new default context for all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"async operations in that thread. In this case you may not need to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ever call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"text":"], assuming you want","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the new [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] to be the default for the whole lifecycle","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the thread.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don’t have control over how the new thread was created (e.g."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the new thread isn’t newly created, or if the thread life"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cycle is managed by a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"), it is always suggested to wrap"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the logic that needs to use the new [struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"text":"] inside a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] \/","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"text":"] pair, otherwise threads that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"are re-used will end up never explicitly releasing the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"] reference they hold.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In some cases you may want to schedule a single operation in a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"non-default context, or temporarily use a non-default context in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the main thread. In that case, you can wrap the call to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"asynchronous operation inside a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] \/"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"text":"] pair, but it is up to you to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ensure that no other asynchronous operations accidentally get"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"started while the non-default context is active.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Beware that libraries that predate this function may not correctly"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"handle being used from a thread with a thread-default context. For example,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"see ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_file_supports_thread_contexts()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextRef":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContextRef"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"MainContextRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextref","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContextRef"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMainContext"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","title":"MainContext"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextRef/MainContextProtocol-Implementations":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextref\/maincontextprotocol-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef\/MainContextProtocol-Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","title":"MainContextProtocol Implementations","kind":"article"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPool":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct represents a thread pool.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ThreadPool","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/threadpool"},"../gio/index.html":{"identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","title":"Gio","url":"..\/gio\/index.html","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Gio","type":"text"}],"type":"link"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainLoop":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainLoop","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMainLoop"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"representing the main event loop of a GLib or GTK application."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mainloop","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainLoop"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","title":"MainLoop"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextRef/pushThreadDefault()":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pushThreadDefault"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Acquires ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(such as most "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"-based I\/O) which are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"started in this thread to run under ","type":"text"},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and deliver their","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"changes the context returned by [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not the one returned by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.default"},{"type":"text","text":"], so it does not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"affect the context used by functions like [func"},{"code":"GLib.idle_add","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"title":"pushThreadDefault()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextRef\/pushThreadDefault()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextref\/pushthreaddefault()","kind":"symbol","type":"topic"}}}